criteria.textblock:
        Inclusion Criteria:

          -  Bipolar Disorder, type I; Cocaine Dependence with use in the past 7 days; Currently
             taking a mood stabilizer; Meets criteria for a hypomanic or manic episode

        Exclusion Criteria:

          -  Bipolar Disorder, type II, NOS; Cyclothymia; Other substance dependence; Diabetes;
             Initiated therapy in the past 2 weeks; History of cataracts or likely cataracts;
             Current active suicidal or homicidal ideation; Life threatening medical condition;
             Mental retardation, dementia or severe cognitive impairment; Pregnant or nursing
             womenon; antipsychotic within 7 days of beginning Quetiapine therapy or have initiated
             antidepressants or mood stabilizers or psychotherapy within the past two weeks.
